<br>
If you are attempting to suggest that WTG's cost $1000/Kw as opposed to nuclear costing $3000/Kw I would suggest that you may be being a bit misleading<!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
For those that don't know. WTG's outputs are normally rated for a 25 MPH wind speed. the relationship between wind speed and power output is not linear, its not even a square. It is a cube!<!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :smash --><img src=http://pages.prodigy.net/rogerlori1/emoticons/smashf.gif ALT=":smash"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
In a 20 MPH wind your 1.5Mw WTG is only producing 750Kw!<br>
<br>
In a 15MPH wind (a reasonable average for even quite windy sites) we are only getting just over 300Kw All of a sudden WTG's don't look so economical after all. Our $1000/Kw WTG has turned into a nuclear busting $5000/Kw<br>
<br>
<br>
Im not (for now) even going to go down the route of how much land you need to site the 5000 or so machines that we would need to cover the output of a single reactor (a power *plant* may have several reactors!) <br>
<br>
Sufice to say that, although one WTG can look fairly majestic, having them dotted all over the landscape as far as the eye can see would not only present a ghastly eyesore (you may be able to hide things like that in the US but we simply don't have enough land in the UK!) they would present a threat to wildlife, they would be *very* noisy (Cue Apocylipse-now helicopter noises, but much louder<!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :( --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/frown.gif ALT=":("><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> ), and they would completly mess up radio, TV, radar etc for miles around.<br>
<br>
<br>
Given the choice of<br>
<br>
a) Building 10,000 WTG's covering an area of, hell I dont know, 2000Km^2 (on which you wont, in practice, be able to do anything else!)<br>
<br>
b) Building a two reactor power station and planting 2000Km^2 of new forrest. (which can be a Carbon sink, visual and recreational amenity and wildlife refuge)<br>
<br>
Option B every time!<br>
<br>
